<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA4FFEAD1DBCAB5FE2E15C0" blockId="6.[136,487,1922,1949]" box="[136,487,1922,1949]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading id="B22C2865FFA4FFEAD1DBCAB5FE2E15C0" bold="true" box="[136,487,1922,1949]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="1">
<emphasis id="DBAF431BFFA4FFEAD1DBCAB5FE2E15C0" bold="true" box="[136,487,1922,1949]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="2EDBE48AFFA4FFEAD0D1CAB5FE2E15C0" authorityName="A. Braun" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Seringe ex de Candolle" box="[386,487,1922,1949]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBAF431BFFA4FFEAD0D1CAB5FE2E15C0" bold="true" box="[386,487,1922,1949]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Sorbaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<footnote id="8AC08307FFA4FFEAD1DBCAF0FA621A48" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA4FFEAD1DBCAF0FA621A48" blockId="6.[136,1452,1990,2070]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">1. Shrub up to 3 m, usually less than 2 m; follicles and ovaries densely hairy; inflorescences erect, narrowly spreading branches; sepals triangular, apex acute, longer than broad, glandular hair along the margin; stamens usually 30 or more, equal and longer than petals...................................................................................................................................................................................................2</paragraph>
</footnote>
<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA5FFEBD1DBCD97FA62128C" blockId="7.[136,1452,159,411]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
- Shrub up to 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD01CCD97FEB112E8" box="[335,376,160,181]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="7.0">7 m</quantity>
, usually more than 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD368CDA8FDAD12E8" box="[571,612,159,181]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
; follicles and ovaries glabrous; inflorescences pendulous, widely spreading branches; sepals semicircular, apex obtuse, broader than long, glabrous; stamens usually 20, equal to the petals ...........................................3
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA5FFEBD1DBCDEEFA63137A" blockId="7.[136,1452,159,411]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
2. Shrub 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD041CDEEFE9B12B3" box="[274,338,217,238]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 m</quantity>
; inflorescences composed of numerous flowers; flowers 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD226CDEFFC1812B3" box="[885,977,216,238]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10 mm</quantity>
in diameter; petals 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD5DCCDEFFACB12B3" box="[1167,1282,216,238]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="3.6" valueMax="5.9" valueMin="1.3">1.3–5.9 mm</quantity>
long; sepals 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD4D2CDEEFED51356" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="0.7">0.7– 2.5 mm</quantity>
long; Northern 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD0E5CDC2FE261356" box="[438,495,245,267]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">China</collectingCountry>
(including 
<collectingRegion id="2B1F51EBFFA5FFEBD30DCDC1FD311356" box="[606,760,245,267]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Inner Mongolia</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD25BCDC1FC881356" box="[776,833,246,267]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD218CDC1FC411356" box="[843,904,246,267]" name="South Korea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Korea</collectingCountry>
, and Russian Far East (including Kamchatka Peninsula). .......................................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="2EDBE48AFFA5FFEBD466CC24FA63137A" authorityName="A. Braun" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[1333,1450,274,296]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sorbifolia">
<emphasis id="DBAF431BFFA5FFEBD466CC24FA63137A" box="[1333,1450,274,296]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">S. sorbifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA5FFEBD1DBCC07FA62133C" blockId="7.[136,1452,159,411]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
- Shrub 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD042CC18FEBA1318" box="[273,371,303,325]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="0.35" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.5 m</quantity>
; inflorescences composed of few flowers; flowers 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD206CC18FC721318" box="[853,955,303,325]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15 mm</quantity>
in diameter; petals 4.0– 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD5F3CC18FB211318" box="[1184,1256,303,325]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
long; sepals 
<quantity id="2E2332ECFFA5FFEBD430CC18FF31133C" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="mm" value="2.4" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="1.4">1.4–3.4 mm</quantity>
long; Russian Far East (Lake Baikal)............................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="2EDBE48AFFA5FFEBD418CC7BFA62133C" box="[1355,1451,332,353]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pallasii">
<emphasis id="DBAF431BFFA5FFEBD418CC7BFA62133C" box="[1355,1451,332,353]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">S. pallasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA5FFEBD1DBCC5EFA621323" blockId="7.[136,1452,159,411]" box="[136,1451,361,383]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
3. Style recurving, fixed at or near the apex of the follicle; 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD3BECC5EFCAC1322" box="[749,869,361,383]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD23CCC5EFC6A1322" box="[879,931,361,383]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD2FFCC5EFC211322" box="[940,1000,361,383]" name="Nepal" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD549CC5EFBA21322" box="[1050,1131,361,383]" name="Pakistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
................................ 
<taxonomicName id="2EDBE48AFFA5FFEBD463CC5EFA621323" authorityName="Rehder" authorityYear="1938" baseAuthorityName="Lindley" box="[1328,1451,361,382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis id="DBAF431BFFA5FFEBD463CC5EFA621323" box="[1328,1451,361,382]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">S. tomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA5FFEBD1DBCCB1FA6313C7" blockId="7.[136,1452,159,411]" box="[136,1450,389,411]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
- Style fixed much below the apex of the follicle; Central and southern 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD223CCB2FC6513C6" box="[880,940,389,411]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD2E6CCB1FC2713C6" box="[949,1006,390,411]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="91CCDF99FFA5FFEBD572CCB1FB9513C6" box="[1057,1116,390,411]" name="South Korea" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Korea</collectingCountry>
..................................... 
<taxonomicName id="2EDBE48AFFA5FFEBD412CCB1FA6313C7" authorityName="Maximowicz" authorityYear="1879" baseAuthorityName="Regel &amp; Tiling" box="[1345,1450,389,411]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kirilowii">
<emphasis id="DBAF431BFFA5FFEBD412CCB1FA6313C7" box="[1345,1450,389,411]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">S. kirilowii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9649F09FFA5FFEBD1C5CCFDFC4713B9" blockId="7.[150,910,457,485]" box="[150,910,457,485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
. 
